entries.title: Nine dead as bomb cyclone sends US temperatures to -45C
entries.description: Nine people have died in the US as the country grapples with a winter storm that has seen temperatures plunge as low as -45C (-49F).

entries.title: What we know about the Paris shooting
entries.description: Tragedy has once again struck Paris with three people dead and three others injured following a shooting.

entries.title: Man on FBI most wanted list is arrested in Spanish hotel
entries.description: Spanish police have arrested one of the FBI's most wanted during a raid in Madrid.

entries.title: Two killed and four wounded in shooting in Paris
entries.description: Two people have been killed and four others injured after a gunman opened fire in Paris.

entries.title: Four full months of power cuts fuelling violent crime amid South Africa's electricity crisis
entries.description: South Africa is in the throes of an electricity crisis.

entries.title: French killer 'The Serpent' freed from Nepal jail
entries.description: The French murderer known as "The Serpent" has been freed from prison in Nepal after serving most of his sentence for the murders of American and Canadian backpackers.

entries.title: Trump engaged in 'multi-part conspiracy' to overturn 2020 presidential election result - Jan 6 panel report
entries.description: Donald Trump was engaged in a "multi-part conspiracy" to overturn the lawful results of the 2020 presidential election, according to a report by US politicians.
